UNOA.title: UN/ECE level A
UNOA.description: As defined in the basic code table of ISO 646 with the exceptions of lower case letters, alternative graphic character allocations and national or application-oriented graphic character allocations.

UNOB.title: UN/ECE level B
UNOB.description: As defined in the basic code table of ISO 646 with the exceptions of alternative graphic character allocations and national or application-oriented graphic character allocations.

UNOC.title: UN/ECE level C
UNOC.description: As defined in ISO 8859-1 : Information processing - Part 1: Latin alphabet No. 1.

UNOD.title: UN/ECE level D
UNOD.description: As defined in ISO 8859-2 : Information processing - Part 2: Latin alphabet No. 2.

UNOE.title: UN/ECE level E
UNOE.description: As defined in ISO 8859-5 : Information processing - Part 5: Latin/Cyrillic alphabet.

UNOF.title: UN/ECE level F
UNOF.description: As defined in ISO 8859-7 : Information processing - Part 7: Latin/Greek alphabet.

UNOG.title: UN/ECE level G
UNOG.description: As defined in ISO 8859-3 : Information processing - Part 3: Latin alphabet.

UNOH.title: UN/ECE level H
UNOH.description: As defined in ISO 8859-4 : Information processing - Part 4: Latin alphabet.

UNOI.title: UN/ECE level I
UNOI.description: As defined in ISO 8859-6 : Information processing - Part 6: Latin/Arabic alphabet.

UNOJ.title: UN/ECE level J
UNOJ.description: As defined in ISO 8859-8 : Information processing - Part 8: Latin/Hebrew alphabet.

UNOK.title: UN/ECE level K
UNOK.description: As defined in ISO 8859-9 : Information processing - Part 9: Latin alphabet.

UNOW.title: UN/ECE level W
UNOW.description: ISO 10646-1 octet with code extension technique to support UTF-8 (UCS Transformation Format, 8 bit) encoding.

UNOX.title: UN/ECE level X
UNOX.description: Code extension technique as defined by ISO 2022 utilising the escape techniques in accordance with ISO 2375.

UNOY.title: UN/ECE level Y
UNOY.description: ISO 10646-1 octet without code extension technique.

3.title: Version 3
3.description:
ISO 9735 Amendment 1:1992.  
GS1 Description:
Syntax version number 3. This code can be used with all of the character sets (A, B, C, D, E and F).

14.title: GS1
14.description: Partner identification code assigned by GS1, an international organization of GS1 Member Organizations that manages the GS1 System.

UCD.title: Data element error indication
UCD.description: To identify an erroneous simple, composite or component data element, and to identify the nature of the error.

UCF.title: Functional group response
UCF.description: To identify a functional group in the subject interchange and to indicate acknowledgement or rejection (action taken) of the UNG and UNE segments, and to identify any error related to these segments. Depending on the action code, it may also indicate the action taken on the messages within that functional group.

UCI.title: Interchange response
UCI.description: To identify the subject interchange, to indicate interchange receipt, to indicate acknowledgement or rejection (action taken) of the UNA, UNB and UNZ segments, and to identify any error related to these segments. Depending on the action code, it may also indicate the action taken on the functional groups and messages within that interchange.

UCM.title: Message response
UCM.description: To identify a message in the subject interchange, and to indicate that message's acknowledgement or rejection (action taken), and to identify any error related to the UNH and UNT segments.

UCS.title: Segment error indication
UCS.description: To identify either a segment containing an error or a missing segment, and to identify any error related to the complete segment.

UNA.title: Service string advice
UNA.description: To define the characters selected for use as delimiters and indicators in the rest of the interchange that follows.

UNB.title: Interchange header
UNB.description: To start, identify and specify an interchange.

UNE.title: Functional group trailer
UNE.description: To end and check the completeness of a functional group.

UNG.title: Functional group header
UNG.description: To head, identify and specify a functional group.

UNH.title: Message header
UNH.description: To head, identify and specify a message.

UNS.title: Section control
UNS.description: To separate header, detail and summary sections of a message.

UNT.title: Message trailer
UNT.description: To end and check the completeness of a message.

UNZ.title: Interchange trailer
UNZ.description: To end and check the completeness of an interchange.

A.title: Highest priority
A.description: Requested processing priority is the highest.

1.title: Requested
1.description: Acknowledgement is requested.

1.title: Interchange is a test
1.description: Indicates that the interchange is a test.

5.title: Interchange is aservice provider test
5.description: Indicates that this interchange is a test with a service provider.

EN.title: GS1
EN.description: Partner identification code assigned by GS1, an international organization of GS1 Member Organizations that manages the GS1 System.

UN.title: UN/CEFACT
UN.description:
United Nations Centre for Trade Facilitation and Electronic Business (UN/CEFACT).
GS1 Description:
UN Economic Commission for Europe (UN/ECE), Committee on the development of trade (TRADE), Working Party on facilitation of international trade procedures (WP.4).

4.title: Service message, version 4
4.description:
Service messages approved and issued as a part of ISO 9735/Version 4, for use with that version of the syntax.
Notes: For earlier versions of the UN/EDIFACT CONTRL message, each published by the UN as a stand-alone message, the version number to be used is specified in the message documentation.

D.title: Draft version/UN/EDIFACT Directory
D.description:
Message approved and issued as a draft message (Valid for directories published after March 1993 and prior to March 1997). Message approved as a standard message (Valid for directories published after March 1997).
Message approved as a standard message (Valid for directories published after March 1997).

01B.title: Release 2001 - B
01B.description: Message approved and issued in the second 2001 release of the UNTDID (United Nations Trade Data Interchange Directory).

1.title: First release
1.description: Message approved and issued in the first release of the year of the UNTDID (United Nations Trade Data Interchange Directory).

3.title: Third release, CONTRL message
3.description: Third release of the service message type CONTRL. Approved and issued as document TRADE/WP.4/R.1186/Rev.1 (including Corr.1) for use with version 2 and 3 of the syntax.  Notes: This code shall only be used with the CONTRL message.

EAN001.title: GS1 version control number (GS1 Permanent Code)

EAN002.title: GS1 version control number (GS1 Permanent Code)

EAN003.title: GS1 version control number (GS1 Permanent Code)

EAN004.title: GS1 version control number (GS1 Permanent Code)

EAN005.title: GS1 version control number (GS1 Permanent Code)

EAN006.title: GS1 version control number (GS1 Permanent Code)

EAN007.title: GS1 version control number (GS1 Permanent Code)

EAN008.title: GS1 version control number (GS1 Permanent Code)

EAN009.title: GS1 version control number (GS1 Permanent Code)

EAN010.title: GS1 version control number (GS1 Permanent Code)

EAN011.title: GS1 version control number (GS1 Permanent Code)

GDSN23.title: GDSN version 2.3 (GS1 Permanent Code)
GDSN23.description: Indicates that the message is a Global Data Synchronization Network version 2.3 message

APERAK.title: Application error and acknowledgement message
APERAK.description:
A code to identify the application error and acknowledgement message.
GS1 Description:
The function of this message is: a) to inform a message issuer that his message has been received by the addressee's application and has been rejected due to errors encountered during its processing in the application. b) to acknowledge to a message issuer the receipt of his message by the addressee's application.

AUTACK.title: Secure authentication and acknowledgement message
AUTACK.description: A code to identify the secure authentication and acknowledgement message.

BANSTA.title: Banking status message
BANSTA.description:
A code to identify the banking status message.
GS1 Description:
Message sent by the receiver of a previously sent-message to report on the status of processing of this original message. It indicates, at the application level, the acceptance or rejection of the message or the ability for the receiver of the message to execute or not the instructions received.

CNTCND.title: Contractual conditions message
CNTCND.description:
A code to identify the contractual conditions message.
GS1 Description:
Message sent by a buyer to its supplier or by the supplier to the buyer, providing the contractual conditions of a previously negotiated contract in order to enable the automatic validation of orders and in the verification of invoices prior to payment.

COACSU.title: Commercial account summary message
COACSU.description:
A code to identify the commercial account summary message.
GS1 Description:
A commercial account summary message enables the transmission of commercial data concerning payments made and outstanding items on an account over a period of time. The message may be sent at specific agreed fixed intervals or on demand, and may be sent to and, or, from trading parties, and, or their authorised agents.

COMDIS.title: Commercial dispute message
COMDIS.description:
A code to identify the commercial dispute message.
GS1 Description:
Message providing notice of commercial dispute against one or more invoices is usually raised by the buyer to notify the seller that something was found wrong with the goods delivered or the services rendered (goods damaged, delivery incomplete, delivery late, etc.). The dispute must be resolved before the related invoice can be settled. The message will be used to: - notify a dispute; - correspond about an existing dispute (structured information); - notify the settlement of a dispute. The message will serve at the same time as the dispute notice and as the dispute answer.

CONDRA.title: Drawing administration message
CONDRA.description:
A code to identify the drawing administration message.
GS1 Description:
The message will be used for the administration of each exchange of a set of engineering/CAD files. It will give additional information about the files; for example, their nature, a list of their contents and technical information necessary to interpret them. The whole process of exchanging engineering or CAD (Computer Aided Design) files between different parties within one project will be supported by EDIFACT messages. The message CONDRA is one of these messages.

CONTRL.title: Syntax and service report message
CONTRL.description:
A code to identify the syntax and service report message.  
GS1 Description:
Message syntactically acknowledging or rejecting, with error indication, a received interchange, functional group or message.

CREMUL.title: Multiple credit advice message
CREMUL.description:
A code to identify the multiple credit advice message.  
GS1 Description:
A Multiple Credit Advice message is sent by an Account Servicing Financial Institution to the Account Owner or to a third party, which has agreed bilaterally in advance, that its account(s) has been or will be credited for specified amount(s) on the date(s) indicated, in settlement of the referenced business transaction(s).

DEBMUL.title: Multiple debit advice message
DEBMUL.description:
A code to identify the multiple debit advice message.  
GS1 Description:
A Multiple Debit Advice message is sent by an Account Servicing Financial Institution to the Account Owner or to a third party, which has agreed bilaterally in advance, that its account(s) has been or will be debited for specified amount(s) on the date(s) indicated, in settlement of the referenced business transaction(s).

DELFOR.title: Delivery schedule message
DELFOR.description:
A code to identify the delivery schedule message.  
GS1 Description:
Message from buyer to supplier giving product requirements regarding details for short term delivery instructions and/or medium to long term product/service forecast for planning purposes according to conditions set out in a contract or order. The message can be used to authorize the commitment of labour and materials resources.

DESADV.title: Despatch advice message
DESADV.description:
A code to identify the despatch advice message.  
GS1 Description:
A message specifying details for goods despatched or ready for despatch under agreed conditions. The United Nations Despatch Advice Message serves both as a specification for Delivery Despatch Advice and also as a Returns Despatch Advice message.

DIRDEB.title: Direct debit message
DIRDEB.description:
A code to identify the direct debit message.  
GS1 Description:
Message sent by the creditor to the creditor's bank instructing it to claim specified amounts from the debtor(s) and to credit these amounts to a single account it services for the creditor in settlement of the referenced transaction(s).

FINCAN.title: Financial cancellation message
FINCAN.description:
A code to identify the financial cancellation message.  
GS1 Description:
A Financial Cancellation Message is sent by the Ordering Customer (or Payor or Agent on behalf of the Ordering Customer) or by a third party having authority on the Ordering Customer's payments to the Ordered Bank to request cancellation of a given financial message or transaction.

FINSTA.title: Financial statement of an account message
FINSTA.description:
A code to identify the financial statement of an account message.  
GS1 Description:
This message can be used to cater for various communication functions between financial institutions and their customers. The most frequent function is to provide a statement of booked items confirming entries on a customer's account. The message type may contain several accounts (quoted in the B-level).

GENRAL.title: General purpose message
GENRAL.description:
A code to identify the general purpose message.  
GS1 Description:
A message to enable the transmission of textual information.

HANMOV.title: Cargo/goods handling and movement message
HANMOV.description:
code to identify the cargo/goods handling and movement message.  
GS1 Description:
Message from a party to a warehouse/distribution centre identifying the handling services and where required the movement of specified goods, limited to warehouses within the jurisdiction of the distribution centre.

IFCSUM.title: Forwarding and consolidation summary message
IFCSUM.description:
A code to identify the forwarding and consolidation summary message.  
GS1 Description:
Message used for consolidation purposes from a party arranging forwarding and transport services to the party for which the transport of the consolidated cargo is destined. The message can be used to exchange information concerning the consolidated cargo between forwarders, carriers and agents enabling those parties to handle the consignments included in the consolidation. In addition it can be used for a collection of consignments originating from one shipper for forwarding and transport services.

IFTMAN.title: Arrival notice message
IFTMAN.description:
A code to identify the arrival notice message.  
GS1 Description:
Message from the party providing forwarding and/or transport services to the party such as has been indicated in the contract, giving notice and details of the arrival of the consignment.

IFTMBC.title: Booking confirmation message
IFTMBC.description:
A code to identify the booking confirmation message.  
GS1 Description:
Message from the party providing forwarding and/or transport services to the party booking those services giving the confirmation information to the booking of the consignment concerned. A confirmation might read that the booking of a consignment is accepted, pending, conditionally accepted or rejected. The conditions under which requested services take place may be given in this message.

IFTMBF.title: Firm booking message
IFTMBF.description:
A code to identify the firm booking message.  
GS1 Description:
Message from a party definitely booking forwarding and/or transport services for a consignment to the party providing those services. The message will contain the conditions under which the sender of the messages requires the services to take place.

IFTMIN.title: Instruction message
IFTMIN.description:
A code to identify the instruction message.  
GS1 Description:
Message from the party issuing an instruction regarding forwarding/transport services for a consignment under conditions agreed, to the party arranging the forwarding and/or transport services.

IFTSTA.title: International multimodal status report message
IFTSTA.description:
A code to idA code to identify the international multimodal status report message.  
GS1 Description:
Message to report the transport status and/or a change in the transport status (i.e. event) between agreed parties.ntify the international multimodal status report message.

INSDES.title: Instruction to despatch message
INSDES.description:
A code to identify the instruction to despatch message.  
GS1 Description:
A message instructing a third party to despatch a delivery.

INVOIC.title: Invoice message
INVOIC.description:
A code to identify the invoice message.  
GS1 Description:
Message claiming payment for goods or services supplied under conditions agreed between the seller and the buyer. The UNSM invoice message, with correct data qualification, serves also as the specification for debit note and credit note messages.

INVRPT.title: Inventory report message
INVRPT.description:
A code to identify the inventory report message.  
GS1 Description:
Message specifying information relating to held inventories. The inventory report message is intended to be used in either direction between trading partners.

KEYMAN.title: Security key and certificate management message
KEYMAN.description: A code to identify the security key and certificate management message.

MSCONS.title: Metered services consumption report message
MSCONS.description:
A code to identify the metered services consumption report message.  
GS1 Description:
A metered services consumption report is a communication between trading parties, or their agents, providing consumption and where required associated technical information at a location(s) for a product(s) or service(s) where the supply is recorded using a meter(s).

ORDCHG.title: Purchase order change request message
ORDCHG.description:
A code to identify the purchase order change request message.  
GS1 Description:
Message from the buyer to the seller, specifying details of the buyer's request to change a purchase order.

ORDERS.title: Purchase order message
ORDERS.description:
A code to identify the purchase order message.  
GS1 Description:
Message specifying details for goods or services ordered under conditions agreed between the seller and the buyer.

ORDRSP.title: Purchase order response message
ORDRSP.description:
A code to identify the purchase order response message.  
GS1 Description:
Message from the seller to the buyer, responding to a purchase order message or a purchase order change request message.

OSTENQ.title: Order status enquiry message
OSTENQ.description:
A code to identify the order status enquiry message.  
GS1 Description:
A message from a buyer or buyer's agent which requests a supplier or supplier's agent for information on the current status of a previously sent outstanding order(s).

OSTRPT.title: Order status report message
OSTRPT.description:
A code to identify the order status report message.  
GS1 Description:
A message by means of which a seller or seller's agent reports status information on an order. This may be a reply to an order status enquiry sent by a buyer or buyer's agent or a report as agreed between trading parties.

PARTIN.title: Party information message
PARTIN.description:
A code to identify the party information message.  
GS1 Description:
Message to enable the transmission of basic information regarding locations and the related operational, administrative, financial, manufacturing and trading data.

PAYDUC.title: Payroll deductions advice message
PAYDUC.description:
A code to identify the payroll deductions advice message.
Notes:
1. The versions of this message which appear in message directories up to and including the D.99B directory are for use with Version 3 or 4 of the ISO 9735 syntax. Versions of the message which appear in the D.00A and later directories shall be used only with Version 4 of the ISO 9735 syntax.
2. This code value is retained in the Version 3 service code list for information purposes only.  
GS1 Description:
Message sent by a party to a service providing organisation, to detail payments by payroll deductions, on behalf of employees, made to the service providing organisation.

PAYMUL.title: Multiple payment order message
PAYMUL.description:
A code to identify the multiple payment order message.  
GS1 Description:
Message sent by the ordering customer (or payor or agent on behalf of the ordering customer) to the ordered bank, to instruct the ordered bank to debit an account it services for the ordering customer, and to arrange for the payment of specified amounts to several beneficiaries (or payees) in settlement of the referenced business transaction(s).

PRICAT.title: Price/sales catalogue message
PRICAT.description:
A code to identify the price/sales catalogue message.  
GS1 Description:
Message to enable the transmission of information regarding pricing and catalogue details for goods and services offered by a seller to a buyer.

PRODAT.title: Product data message
PRODAT.description:
A code to identify the product data message.  
GS1 Description:
A product data message is a communication between parties containing master data, to identify and describe products available for supply or for information purposes. This information of long validity does not include commercial terms and conditions but technical and functional product descriptions.

PROINQ.title: Product inquiry message
PROINQ.description:
A code to identify the product inquiry message.  
GS1 Description:
A message enabling the sender to inquire on a product or group of products from a master product catalogue or file according to criteria defined in the message.

QALITY.title: Quality data message
QALITY.description:
A code to identify the quality data message.  
GS1 Description:
Message to enable the transmission of the results of tests performed to satisfy a specified product or process requirement. The content includes, but it is not limited to, test data and measurements, statistical information, and the testing methods employed.

QUOTES.title: Quote message
QUOTES.description:
A code to identify the quote message.  
GS1 Description:
Message which provides potential sellers with the ability to provide price, delivery schedule, and other conditions for potential sales of goods or services.

RECADV.title: Receiving advice message
RECADV.description:
A code to identify the receiving advice message.  
GS1 Description:
This message is to address the business needs related to the goods receipt. This message is used to report the physical receipt of goods. The message allows for the reporting of discrepancies in products, quantities, terms, packages, etc.

REMADV.title: Remittance advice message
REMADV.description:
A code to identify the remittance advice message.  
GS1 Description:
Message which provides a detailed accounting relative to a payment, or other form of financial settlement, on a specified date for the provision of goods and/or services as detailed in the advice.

REQOTE.title: Request for quote message
REQOTE.description:
A code to identify the request for quote message.  
GS1 Description:
Message which provides potential buyers with the ability to solicit price, delivery schedule, and other conditions from potential sellers of goods or services.

RETANN.title: Announcement for returns message
RETANN.description:
A code to identify the announcement for returns message.  
GS1 Description:
Message announcing returns.

RETINS.title: Instruction for returns message
RETINS.description:
A code to identify the instruction for returns message.  
GS1 Description:
Message instructing on returns.

SLSFCT.title: Sales forecast message
SLSFCT.description:
A code to identify the sales forecast message.  
GS1 Description:
Message to enable the transmission of forecast data related to products or services, such as corresponding location, period, product identification, pricing, monetary amount, quantity, market sector information, sales parties. It enables the recipient to process the information automatically and use it for production, planning, marketing, statistical purposes, etc.

SLSRPT.title: Sales data report message
SLSRPT.description:
A code to identify the sales data report message.  
GS1 Description:
Message to enable the transmission of sales data related to products or services, such as corresponding location, period, product identification, pricing, monetary amount, quantity, market sector information, sales parties. It enables the recipient to process the information automatically and use it for production, planning, marketing, statistical purposes, etc.

TAXCON.title: Tax control message
TAXCON.description:
A code to identify the tax control message.  
GS1 Description:
A message to enable the transmission of information related to the tax details of an invoice, or a batch/batches of invoice messages.

D.title: Header/detail section separation
D.description: To qualify the segment UNS, when separating the header from the detail section of a message.

S.title: Detail/summary section separation
S.description: To qualify the segment UNS, when separating the detail from the summary section of a message.

1.title: Acknowledged (this level and all lower levels) (GS1 Permanent Code)
1.description: The currently identified interchange is acknowledged.

2.title: Acknowledged - errors detected and reported (GS1 Permanent Code)
2.description: The currently identified interchange is acknowledged but errors have been detected and reported.

3.title: One or more rejected - next lower level (GS1 Permanent Code)
3.description: Information from the next lower level in the currently identified interchange has been rejected.

4.title: This level and all lower levels rejected
4.description: The corresponding referenced-level and all its lower referenced-levels are rejected. One or more errors are reported at this reporting-level or a lower reporting- level.

5.title: UNB/UNZ accepted (GS1 Permanent Code)
5.description: The currently identified interchange has been accepted.

6.title: UNB/UNZ rejected (GS1 Permanent Code)
6.description: The currently identified interchange has been rejected.

7.title: This level acknowledged, next lower level acknowledged if not explicitly rejected
7.description:
The corresponding referenced level is acknowledged. All messages or functional groups at the next lower referenced level are acknowledged except those explicitly reported as rejected at the next lower reporting level in this CONTRL message.
GS1 Description:
The corresponding referenced-level is acknowledged. All messages or functional groups at the next lower referenced-level are acknowledged except those explicitly reported as rejected at the next lower reporting-level in this CONTRL message.

8.title: Interchange received
8.description: Indication of interchange receipt implies that the recipient of the subject interchange: has received the interchange; and acknowledges the parts of the interchange that have been checked in order to assure that the data elements copied into the reporting UCI segment are syntactically correct; and has accepted liability for notifying the sender of acknowledgement or rejection of the other parts of the interchange; and has taken reasonable precautions in order to ensure that the sender is so notified.

1.title: UNA not supported (GS1 Permanent Code)
1.description: Notification that the UNA character string cannot be understood or complied with.

11.title: Password invalid (GS1 Permanent Code)
11.description: Indication that the password in segment UNB is invalid.

12.title: Invalid value
12.description: Notification that the value of a simple data element, composite data element or component data element does not conform to the relevant specifications for the value.

13.title: Missing
13.description: Notification that a mandatory (or otherwise required) service or user segment, data element, composite data element or component data element is missing

14.title: Value not supported in this position
14.description: Notification that the recipient does not support use of the specific value of an identified simple data element, composite data element or component data element in the position where it is used. The value may be valid according to the relevant specifications and may be supported if it is used in another position.

15.title: Not supported in this position
15.description: Notification that the recipient does not support use of the segment type, simple data element type, composite data element type or component data element type in the specific in the identified position.

16.title: Too many constituents
16.description: Notification that the identified segment contained to many data elements or that the identified composite data element contained too many component data elements.

17.title: No agreement
17.description: No agreement exist that allows receipt of an interchange, functional group or message with the value of the identified simple data element, composite data element or component data element.

18.title: Unspecified error
18.description: Notification that an error has been identified, but the nature of the error is not reported.

19.title: Invalid decimal notation
19.description: Notification that the character indicated as decimal notation in UNA is invalid, or the decimal notation used in a data element is not consistent with the one indicated in UNA.

2.title: Syntax level or version not supported
2.description: Notification that the syntax version and/or level is not supported by the recipient.

20.title: Character invalid as service character
20.description: Notification that a character advised in UNA is invalid as service character.

21.title: Invalid character(s)
21.description: Notification that one or more character(s) used in the interchange is not a valid character as defined by the syntax level indicated in UNB. The invalid character is part of the referenced-level, or followed immediately after the identified part of the interchange.

22.title: Invalid service character(s)
22.description: Notification that the service character(s) used in the interchange is not a valid service character as advised in UNA or not one of the service characters in the syntax level indicated in UNB or defined in an interchange agreement. If the code is used in UCS or UCD, the invalid character followed immediately after the identified part of the interchange.

23.title: Unknown interchange sender
23.description: Notification that the Interchange sender (S002) is unknown.

24.title: Too old
24.description: Notification that the received interchange or functional group is older than a limit specified in an IA or determined by the recipient.

25.title: Test indicator not supported
25.description: Notification that a test processing could not be performed for the identified interchange, functional group or message.

26.title: Duplicate detected
26.description: Notification that a possible duplication of a previously received interchange, functional group or message has been detected. The earlier transmission may have been rejected.

27.title: Security function not supported
27.description: Notification that a security function related to the referenced-level or data element is not supported.

28.title: References do not match
28.description: Notification that the control reference in UNB/UNG/UNH does not match the one in UNZ/UNE/UNT.

29.title: Control count does not match number of instances received
29.description: Notification that the number of functional groups/ messages/segments does not match the number given in UNZ/UNE/UNT.

3.title: Message version/release not supported (GS1 Permanent Code)
3.description: Notification that the message type, version number and/or release number in the UNG and/or UNH segments are not supported by the recipient.

30.title: Functional groups and messages mixed
30.description: Notification that individual messages and functional groups have been mixed at the same level in the interchange.

31.title: More than one message type in group
31.description: Notification that different message types are contained in a functional group.

32.title: Lower level empty
32.description: Notification that the interchange did not contain any messages or functional groups, or a functional group did not contain any messages.

33.title: Invalid occurrence outside message or functional group
33.description: Notification that an invalid segment or data element occurred in the interchange, between messages or between functional groups. Rejection is reported at the level above.

34.title: Nesting indicator not allowed
34.description: Notification that explicit nesting has been used in a message where it shall not be used.

35.title: Too many segment repetitions
35.description: Notification that a segment was repeated too many times.

36.title: Too many segment group repetitions
36.description: Notification that a segment group is repeated to many times.

37.title: Invalid type of character(s)
37.description: Notification that one or more numeric characters were used in an alphabetic (component) data element or that one or more alphabetic characters were used in a numeric (component) data element.

38.title: Missing digit in front of decimal sign
38.description: Notification that a decimal sign is not preceded by one or more digits.

39.title: Data element too long
39.description: Notification that the length of the data element received exceeded the maximum length specified in the data element description.

40.title: Data element too short
40.description: Notification that the length of the data element received is shorter than the minimum length specified in the data element description.

41.title: Permanent communication network error
41.description: Notification that a permanent error was reported by the communication network used for transfer of the interchange. Re-transmission of an identical interchange with the same parameters at network level will not succeed.

42.title: Temporary communication network error
42.description: Notification that a temporary error was reported by the communication network used for transfer of the interchange. Re-transmissions of an identical interchange may succeed.

43.title: Unknown interchange recipient

A message between parties containing master data, to identify and describe products available for supply or for information purposes. This information of long validity does not include commercial terms and conditions but technical and functional product descriptions.

376.description:

GS1 Description:
An initial download and any future changes made to the data within the standing request is automatically sent to the buyer as they occur, until the standing request is cancelled.
Notes:
A standing product inquiry implies that the supplier will send both a one-time download and notification of all future changes to the requested trade item until the standing request is deleted. A standing product inquiry can only be modified by deleting the original request and initiating a new request.

location, time period, product identification, pricing and quantity information. It enables the recip.

90E.title: Cargo/goods handling and movement message (GS1 Temporary Code)
90E.description:
A message from a party to a warehouse, distribution centre, or logistics service provider identifying the handling services and where required the movement of specified goods, limited to warehouses within the jurisdiction of the distribution centre or logistics service provider.
GS1 Note: Code marked for deletion. Use value 738 instead.

910.title: Import licence, application for
910.description: Document/message in which an interested party applies to the competent body for authorization to import either a limited quantity of articles subject to import restrictions, or an unlimited quantity of such articles during a limited period, and specifies the kind of articles, their origin and value, etc.

911.title: Import licence
911.description: Document/message issued by the competent body in accordance with import regulations in force, by which authorization is granted to a named party to import either a limited quantity of designated articles or an unlimited quantity of such articles during a limited period, under conditions specified in the document.

938.title: Tax declaration (general)
938.description: Document/message containing a general tax declaration.

94E.title: Metered services consumption report invoice support (GS1 Temporary Code)
94E.description:
A Metered Services Consumption Report is a communication between trading parties, or their agents, providing consumption and where required associated technical information at a location(s) for a product(s) or service(s) where the supply is recorded using a meter(s) to support information contained in commercial invoices.
GS1 Note: Code marked for deletion. Use value 739 instead.

951.title: TIF forms
951.description: International Customs transit document by which the sender declares goods for carriage by rail in accordance with the provisions of the 1952 International Convention to facilitate the crossing of frontiers for goods carried by rail (TIF Convention of UIC).

952.title: TIR Carnet
952.description: International Customs document (International Transit by Road), issued by a guaranteeing association approved by the Customs authorities, under the cover of which goods are carried, in most cases under Customs seal, in road vehicles and/or containers in compliance with the requirements of the Customs TIR Convention of the International Transport of Goods under cover of TIR Carnets (UN/ECE).

954.title: EUR 1 certificate of origin
954.description: Customs certificate used in preferential goods interchanges between EC countries and EC external countries

991.title: Government contract
991.description: Document/message describing a contract with a government authority

99E.title: Metered services consumption report (GS1 Temporary Code)
99E.description:
A Metered Services Consumption Report is a communication between trading parties, or their agents, providing consumption and where required associated technical information at a location(s) for a product(s) or service(s) where the supply is recorded using a meter(s).
GS1 Note: Code marked for deletion. Use value 742 instead.

YA3.title: Payroll deductions advice (GS1 Temporary Code)
YA3.description:
A message sent by a party (usually an employer or its representative) to a service providing organisation, to detail payroll deductions paid on behalf of its employees to the service providing organisation.
GS1 Note: Code marked for deletion. Use value 747 instead.

YA5.title: Intermediate handling cross docking despatch advice (GS1 Temporary Code)
YA5.description: Document by means of which the supplier or consignor informs the buyer, consignee or the distribution centre about the despatch of goods needing intermediate handling.

YA6.title: Pre-packed cross docking [transshipment] despatch advice (GS1 Temporary Code)
YA6.description: Document by means of which the supplier or consignor informs the buyer, consignee or distribution centre about the despatch of pre-packed goods.

YA7.title: Consignment despatch advice (GS1 Temporary Code)
YA7.description:
Document/message by means of which the supplier informs the buyer about the despatch of goods ordered on consignment (goods to be delivered into stock with agreement on payment when goods are sold out of this stock).
GS1 Note: Code marked for deletion. Use value 748 instead.

YB3.title: Ready for transshipment despatch advice (GS1 Temporary Code)
YB3.description: Document/message by means of which the supplier or consignor informs the buyer, consignee or the distribution center that the goods ordered are ready for transshipment.

YB4.title: Media campaign document (GS1 Temporary Code)
YB4.description: Document providing the details of a media campaign

YB5.title: Product Marketing document, detailed (GS1 Temporary Code)
YB5.description: Marketing document providing a detailed functional description of a product or goods/services.

YB6.title: Product Marketing document, concise (GS1 Temporary Code)
YB6.description: Marketing document providing a concise functional description of a product or goods/services.

YB7.title: Self billed debit note correction (GS1 Temporary Code)
YB7.description: Debit note message that includes revised information differing from an earlier submission of the same debit note in a self billing environment.

YB8.title: Debit note correction (GS1 Temporary Code)
YB8.description: Debit note message that includes revised information differing from an earlier submission of the same debit note.

1.description: The document line is included in the document/transaction.

2.title: Excluded from document/ transaction
2.description: The document line is excluded from the document/transaction.

157.title: Clearing code
157.description: Identification of the responsible bank/clearing house which has cleared or is ordered to do the clearing.  Notes: This code value will be removed effective with directory D.04A.

166.title: Social security identification
166.description: Code assigned by the authority competent to issue social security identification to identify a person.  Notes: This code value will be removed effective with directory D.04A.

174.title: Citizen identification
174.description:
Self explanatory.
Notes:
This code value will be removed effective with directory D.04A.

Code issued by national authority competent to issue citizen identification to identify a person.

1E.description: Incoterms 1990 as published by the International Chamber of Commerce (ICC).

3E.title: Incoterms 2010 (GS1 Permanent Code)
3E.description: Incoterms 2010 as published by the International Chamber of Commerce (ICC).

ADR.title: Accord Europeen au transport international dangereuses (GS1 Permanent Code)
ADR.description: A European agreement concerning the international carriage of dangerous goods by road.

BR.title: Brand (GS1 Permanent Code)
BR.description: An identifying mark or label on the products of a particular company, or the kind or make of a commodity.

CA.title: Category (GS1 Permanent Code)
CA.description: A class or division in a scheme of classification.

CO.title: Colour (GS1 Permanent Code)
CO.description: Description of the colour required/available on the goods.

HMT.title: Hazardous material standard text (GS1 Permanent Code)
HMT.description: Code indicating agreed standard text on hazardous materials.

LOC.title: Location Code (GS1 Permanent Code)
LOC.description: This is a code to indicate where the EAS tag is located on the Trade Item. Values include On outside of Trade Item, Concealed inside Trade Item, Integrated Inside Trade Item.

OAG.title: Organic Claim Agency (GS1 Permanent Code)
OAG.description: A governing body that creates and maintain standards related to organic products.

OCO.title: Organic Trade Item Code (GS1 Permanent Code)
OCO.description: Used to indicate the organic status of a trade item or of one or more of its components.

OUM.title: Ordering unit of measure (GS1 Permanent Code)
OUM.description: The alternate Unit of Measure of how Trade Items are ordered by the Retailer under one Unit of Measure, but sold under another Unit of Measure.

SKB.title: SKRS recommendation (GS1 Permanent Code)
SKB.description: SKRS recommendation for standard clothes hanger.

SRN.title: Service relation number (GS1 Permanent Code)
SRN.description: A number used to identify a database entry which records recurring services, e.g., treatment of a patient in a hospital, usage by a member of a library facilities, etc.

ST.title: Style (GS1 Permanent Code)
ST.description: Specific or characteristic design in any goods.

SUM.title: Selling unit of measure (GS1 Permanent Code)
SUM.description: Describes the measurement used for selling unit of the Trade Item to the end consumer.

SZ.title: Size (GS1 Permanent Code)
SZ.description: Any of a series of graded classifications of measure into which goods are divided.

SZG.title: Size Group (GS1 Permanent Code)
SZG.description: A description of the variable size that is necessary to uniquely specify the size of the item in conjunction with the nonpackaged size dimension.

TYP.title: Type Code (GS1 Permanent Code)
TYP.description: This is a code to indicate the type of EAS tag located on the Trade Item. Values include Acousto-Magnetic, Electro-Magnetic, Ink or dye, Microwave, Radio Frequency.

X11.title: Diet Allergen (GS1 Permanent Code)
X11.description: Indication of which dietary or allergen marks that are on the package.

X12.title: Environment (GS1 Permanent Code)
X12.description: Indication of which environmental marks (e.g. recycling schemes) that are on trade item package.

X13.title: Ethical (GS1 Permanent Code)
X13.description: Indication of which ethical trading marks that are on the package.

X14.title: Free Form (GS1 Permanent Code)
X14.description: Indication of which free-from marks that are on the package.

X15.title: Expiration date (GS1 Permanent Code)
X15.description: Indicates the type of expiration date marked on the packaging.

X16.title: Nesting Direction (GS1 Permanent Code)
X16.description: Depicts the arrangement of two items that nest together specifically whether they nest against each other or on top of each other.

X17.title: Package Marks Hygienic (GS1 Permanent Code)
X17.description: Indication of which hygiene markings are present in the product package

X18.title: Hazardous Components are Removable (GS1 Permanent Code)
X18.description: An indicator if any hazardous components contained within the trade item can easily be separated from the other materials to facilitate product recycling.

X19.title: Trade Item Has Refuse Obligations (GS1 Permanent Code)
X19.description: Indicates if there are special disposal obligations that apply to the trade item for example INTRASTAT.

X20.title: Trade Item Is Designed for Easy Disassembly (GS1 Permanent Code)
X20.description: Indicates that the trade item is designed for easy disassembly by recycling facilities using standard industry tools.

X21.title: Trade Item Is Rigid Plastic Packaging Container (GS1 Permanent Code)
X21.description: Indicates that a product is or is contained in a Rigid Plastic Packaging Container (RPPC) as defined by laws in the target market.

X22.title: Trade Item Is ROHS Compliant (GS1 Permanent Code)
X22.description: Indicates if the product is compliant with the European Union RoHS Directive.

X23.title: Trade Item Is Universal Waste (GS1 Permanent Code)
X23.description: Indicates if a product can be considered universal waste.

X24.title: Trade Item Is Consumer Upgradeable Or Maintainable (GS1 Permanent Code)
X24.description: Indicates if a product can be easily upgraded or have parts replaced by the consumer.

X25.title: Trade Item Contains Short Chain Chlorinated Paraffins (GS1 Permanent Code)
X25.description: Indicate if the trade item and/or its components contain paints, coatings, plastics or other materials containing short chain chlorinated paraffins (SCCPs).

X26.title: Trade Item Contains Pesticide (GS1 Permanent Code)
X26.description: Indicates if the trade item is advertised or labelled as a chemical or contains a chemical that is advertised or labelled to kill, repel or prevent the growth of any living organism.

X27.title: Trade Item Contains Propellant (GS1 Permanent Code)
X27.description: Indicates if a trade item contains a compressed gas or propellant.

X28.title: Trade Item Contains Polyvinyl Chloride (GS1 Permanent Code)
X28.description: Indicate if product contains Polyvinyl Chloride (PVC), a widely used thermoplastic polymer.

X29.title: Trade Item Chemical Is Not Intended For Human Consumption (GS1 Permanent Code)
X29.description: Indicates that the trade item is or contains a Liquid, Gel, Paste, Powder, or Flammable solid not intended for human consumption (ingested).

X30.title: ROHS Compliance Failure Material (GS1 Permanent Code)
X30.description: The material used in the trade item that does not comply with the ROHS Directives

X31.title: Packaging Terms And Condition (GS1 Permanent Code)
X31.description: Indicates if the packaging given in the described packaging configuration is a rented, exchangeable, against deposit or one way/not reusable.

X32.title: Warranty Effective Date Type (GS1 Permanent Code)
X32.description: The type of date associated with the warranty trade item usually expressed as an event date for the item for example date of purchase, date of manufacture or date of delivery.

X36.title: Seasonal Availability End Date (GS1 Permanent Code)
X36.description: Indicates the end date of the trade item's seasonal availability.

X37.title: Seasonal Availability Start Date  (GS1 Permanent Code)
X37.description: Indicates the start date of the trade item's seasonal availability.

X38.title: Season Calendar Year (GS1 Permanent Code)
X38.description: This element indicates the calendar year in which the trade item is seasonally available.

X39.title: Season Parameter (GS1 Permanent Code)
X39.description: Indication of the season, in which the trade item is available.

X40.title: Trade Item Automatic Power Down is Enabled (GS1 Permanent Code)
X40.description: An indicator whether a product is enabled with auto power down feature when shipped to the customer.

X41.title: Electrical Usage Agency Code (GS1 Permanent Code)
X41.description: The agency that regulates electrical usage for products within a target market.

X42.title: Nesting Type (GS1 Permanent Code)
X42.description: Depicts whether a nested item fits inside or over the other item in a nesting relationship.

X43.title: Display Dimension Type Code (GS1 Permanent Code)
X43.description: Depicts certain display scenarios used for measurement.

X44.title: Manufacturer Has Take Back Program (GS1 Permanent Code)
X44.description: Indicates if the manufacturer of the trade item offers any take back programs to consumers for the product to be reused, remanufactured or recycled by the manufacturer.

X45.title: Display Resolution (GS1 Permanent Code)
X45.description: The display resolution of a television or computer display.

X46.title: Orientation Preference Sequence (GS1 Permanent Code)
X46.description: Depicts the preferred sequence of orientation used to communicate the manufacturers relative preferences of orientation.

X47.title: Orientation Type (GS1 Permanent Code)
X47.description: Depicts via code a display orientation for a trade item.

X48.title: Electrical Usage Trade Item Classification Code (GS1 Permanent Code)
X48.description: A classification code value from a product classification scheme provided to drive required information for electrical usage.

X49.title: Electrical Usage Trade Item Classification Name (GS1 Permanent Code)
X49.description: A classification name from a product classification scheme provided to drive required information for electrical usage.

X50.title: Electrical Usage SubClassification Code (GS1 Permanent Code)
X50.description: A sub-classification code value from a product classification scheme provided to drive required information for electrical usage.

X51.title: Electrical Usage SubClassification Name (GS1 Permanent Code)
X51.description: A sub-classification name provided to drive required information for electrical usage.

X52.title: Confirmation Status Code (GS1 Permanent Code)
X52.description: The CIC Confirmation Code must be of a type of code number that can be generated automatically by a computer system.

X53.title: Confirmation Status Code Description (GS1 Permanent Code)
X53.description: Provides the code description that matches up with the Code that can possibly be generated automatically by a computer system.

X54.title: Additional Confirmation Status Description (GS1 Permanent Code)
X54.description: Provides a way to communicate human entered information that may not be covered by the machine to machine codes and descriptions.

X55.title: Corrective Action (GS1 Permanent Code)
X55.description: Provides the corrective action code to fix the issue that caused the problem.

X56.title: Expected Corrective Information (GS1 Permanent Code)
X56.description: Provides the expected corrective information via a human entered information that may not be covered by the machine to machine codes.

X57.title: Electrical Usage Trade Item Classification Agency (GS1 Permanent Code)
X57.description: A classification agency or organisation whose product classification scheme is being provided to drive required information for electrical usage.

X58.title: ASFIS (GS1 Permanent Code)

GS1 Note: Code marked for deletion. Use value BTG instead.

X6E.title: Nestable percentage (GS1 Temporary Code)
X6E.description:

GS1 Note: Code marked for deletion. Use value BTH instead.

X7E.title: Gross weight including carrier's equipment (GS1 Temporary Code)
X7E.description:
Weight (mass) of goods including packaging and the carrier's equipment. In this context 'carrier's equipment' means any material resources necessary to facilitate the transport and handling of the goods without having the ability to move by its own propulsion, e.g. pallet, container, etc. GS1 usage Note The field of implementation of this code is the area of transport and related activities such as the preparation of goods into consignments for shipping.
GS1 Note: Code marked for deletion. Use value BTI instead.

X8E.title: Peg hole horizontal distance from package leftmost edge (GS1 Temporary Code)
X8E.description:
Horizontal distance from the left most edge of the package to the center of the hole into which the peg is inserted.

E31.title: Square metre per litre

E32.title: Litre per hour
E32.description: A unit of count defining the number of litres per hour.

H87.title: Piece
H87.description: A unit of count defining the number of pieces (piece: a single item, article or exemplar).

BA.title: Base article (GS1 Permanent Code)
BA.description: A conceptual article identified for the purposes of ordering Customer Specific Articles. Base articles must always have configurations of options associated with them.

BLK.title: Bulk consumer unit (GS1 Permanent Code)
BLK.description: The item is designed as a bulk consumer unit, i.e. to be sold mainly to hotels, restaurants, caterers, hospitals etc.

BU.title: Base unit (GS1 Permanent Code)
BU.description: The lowest level packaged unit for a given product, which may or may not be the consumer unit.

CMP.title: Composition (GS1 Permanent Code)
CMP.description: A grouping of existing compositions, base articles, new options, and/or new option values.

CSF.title: Display material (GS1 Permanent Code)
CSF.description: Articles used to promote articles at the sale location.

CSG.title: Full display stand (GS1 Permanent Code)
CSG.description: Display stand containing the articles to be displayed.

CTO.title: Cut to order (GS1 Permanent Code)
CTO.description: Code indicating that the current product may be sold in measurements cut to the customers specification, e.g. carpets.

CU.title: Consumer unit (GS1 Permanent Code)
CU.description: The package size of a product or products agreed by trading partners as the size sold at the retail point of sale.

D.title: Available all the year round (GS1 Permanent Code)
D.description: The product is available all the year round.

DF.title: Default (GS1 Permanent Code)
DF.description: A line item in a Customer Specific Article which is a default option of a base article which will be automatically selected if none of the other available options are chosen.

DIC.title: Discount coupon (GS1 Permanent Code)
DIC.description: A coupon that entitles to a discount.

DST.title: Display stand (GS1 Permanent Code)
DST.description: A stand used for display purposes which is generally not for sale to the consumer.

DU.title: Despatch unit (GS1 Permanent Code)
DU.description: The package size of a product or products which may be shipped when fulfilling an order.

ETO.title: Engineer to Order (GS1 Permanent Code)
ETO.description: Engineer to Order includes products that are designed, developed and manufactured in response to a specific customer request.

FS.title: Available in spring-summer (GS1 Permanent Code)
FS.description: The product is available in the spring-summer period.

HN.title: Handling unit (GS1 Permanent Code)
HN.description: The package size of a product which will be used when transporting and storing the product.

HW.title: Available in autumn-winter (GS1 Permanent Code)
HW.description: The product is available in the autumn-winter period.

IF1.title: IF <> THEN <> ENDIF (GS1 Permanent Code)
IF1.description: E.G., IF <customer chooses node number 1332> THEN <action (taken from DE 1229 of LIN) to node number 1773> ENDIF.

IF2.title: IF NOT <> THEN <> ENDIF (GS1 Permanent Code)
IF2.description: E.G., IF NOT <customer does not choose node number 1332> THEN <action (taken from DE 1229 of LIN) to node number 1773> ENDIF.

IF3.title: IF <> AND (GS1 Permanent Code)
IF3.description: E.G., IF <customer chooses node number 1332> AND (followed by another repeat of IMD with another rule).

IF4.title: IF NOT <> AND (GS1 Permanent Code)
IF4.description: E.G., IF NOT <customer does not choose node number 1332> AND (followed by another repeat of IMD with another rule).

IF5.title: IF <> OR (GS1 Permanent Code)
IF5.description: E.G., IF <customer chooses node number 1332> OR (followed by another repeat of IMD with another rule).

IF6.title: IF NOT <> OR (GS1 Permanent Code)
IF6.description: E.G., IF NOT <customer does not choose node number 1332> OR (followed by another repeat of IMD with another rule).

IF7.title: IF <> XOR (GS1 Permanent Code)
IF7.description: E.G., IF <customer chooses node number 1332> XOR (followed by another repeat of IMD with another rule).

IF8.title: IF NOT <> XOR (GS1 Permanent Code)
IF8.description: E.G., IF NOT <customer does not choose node number 1332> XOR (followed by another repeat of IMD with another rule).

IN.title: Invoicing unit (GS1 Permanent Code)
IN.description: The package size of a product or products which will be used as the unit on which the buyer is invoiced.

IT.title: Intermediate unit (GS1 Permanent Code)
IT.description: A package size of a product or products falling in between two predefined package sizes.

MA.title: Mandatory (GS1 Permanent Code)
MA.description: An option of a Customer Specific Article which is mandatory in the configuration of the base article, e.g. it is mandatory to have legs when ordering a CSA table.

MOD.title: Model (GS1 Permanent Code)
MOD.description: The identification of an article as a high level model of a product, e.g. spring fashions.

MTO.title: Make to Order (GS1 Permanent Code)
MTO.description: A Make to Order environment is one in which products are completed after receipt of a customer order and are built or configured only in response to a customer order.

MTS.title: Make to Stock (GS1 Permanent Code)
MTS.description: Make to Stock products are intended to be shipped from finished goods or off the shelf, are completed prior to receipt of a customer order, and are generally produced in accordance with sales forecasts.

NAR.title: Next Article (GS1 Permanent Code)
NAR.description: An indication that what follows is a set of linked articles, a certain number of these linked articles should be chosen.

NBU.title: Not a base unit (GS1 Permanent Code)
NBU.description: Not the lowest level packaged unit for a given product, which may or may not be the consumer unit.

NCU.title: Not a consumer unit (GS1 Permanent Code)
NCU.description: The current base item or packaging item is not a consumer unit, i.e. is not a pre-packaging that is intended and labelled or marked for consumers according to legal requirements.

NDU.title: Not a despatch unit (GS1 Permanent Code)
NDU.description: The current base item or packaging item is not a regular logistical despatch unit, i.e. it is as a rule only delivered as many within a further repackaging, and not as an individual logistics item.

NFR.title: Not For Resale (GS1 Permanent Code)
NFR.description: Item is not for resale to consumer.

NIN.title: Not an invoicing unit (GS1 Permanent Code)
NIN.description: The current base item or packaging item is not an invoicing unit of the data supplier, i.e. cannot be invoiced individually but only as one of many in a repackaging or transport packaging item.

NLK.title: Not a bulk consumer unit (GS1 Permanent Code)
NLK.description: The item is not designed as a bulk consumer unit, i.e. to be sold mainly to hotels, restaurants, caterers, hospitals etc.

NO.title: Not an ordering unit (GS1 Permanent Code)
NO.description: A package size of a product or products which may not be ordered.

NOS.title: Yes, NOS item (GS1 Permanent Code)
NOS.description: The current item is an NOS (Never out of stock) article, that is continuously reordered and replenished.

NOT.title: Not, not an NOS item (GS1 Permanent Code)
NOT.description: The current item is not an NOS (Never out of stock) article, therefore is not continuously reordered and replenished.

NOV.title: Next option value (GS1 Permanent Code)
NOV.description: An indication that what follows is a set of linked option values, next option values, or parameters.

NPC.title: Reusable container, but not standardized by a pool cooperative (GS1 Permanent Code)
NPC.description: Reusable container that is not standardized by a pool cooperative.

NRC.title: Non-returnable container (GS1 Permanent Code)
NRC.description: The current product is not traditionally a traded product and does not need to be returned to the sender.

NRE.title: Not a retail product (GS1 Permanent Code)
NRE.description: The current item is not meant for retail sale, but only for sale to hotels, restaurants and catering.

NS.title: Not smallest unit (GS1 Permanent Code)
NS.description: Not the smallest unit for a given product.

NSU.title: Non-standard unit (GS1 Permanent Code)
NSU.description: Products grouped together to fulfil specific ordering needs and not generally available.

NVQ.title: Not a variable quantity product (GS1 Permanent Code)
NVQ.description: The current item is a variable weight trade item, for which the weight and the quantity is determined only by the buyer.

OP.title: Option (GS1 Permanent Code)
OP.description: An option within a Customer Specific Article which does not exist on its own, e.g. colour, and which has discrete values.

OPL.title: Overall product level (GS1 Permanent Code)
OPL.description: An overall level whereby many products are grouped on the basis of their composition, application and characteristics (e.g. Coca Cola with no size, packaging, price, etc, specified).

OPV.title: Option value (GS1 Permanent Code)
OPV.description: The result of a choice of an option. The option value will be the lowest level of a branch beneath an option structure.

ORU.title: Ordering unit (GS1 Permanent Code)
ORU.description: Indication that the current product is an ordering unit (ordering unit will not normally equal invoicing unit).

PA.title: Numeric parameter (GS1 Permanent Code)
PA.description: An option of a Customer Specific Article which has a continuous numeric value, e.g., measurement of the length of a chair leg between 60cms and 80cms.

PAA.title: Alpha-numeric parameter (GS1 Permanent Code)
PAA.description: An option of a Customer Specific Article which has a continuous alpha-numeric value, e.g., words and numbers to be embroided into a cushion cover.

PIP.title: Packer or inner pack (GS1 Permanent Code)

PR1.title: Bonus Pack (GS1 Permanent Code)
PR1.description: The free quantity promotional trade item contains free additional quantities. The additional quantity is written on the package as free.

PR2.title: Free components (GS1 Permanent Code)
PR2.description: It contains free included components or material. The price is lower since the trade item includes a part of its content free. The free quantity is written on the package.

PR3.title: Free quantity (GS1 Permanent Code)
PR3.description: It contains free quantity, a special offer sticker on the package indicates the promotional offer but the free quantity is not written on the package. If the free quantity promotional offer results in a change of GTIN and the quantity of prod-uct is the same as the standard trade item, it qualifies as a free quantity promotional trade item. The linkage has to be provided.

PR4.title: Multi-pack and combination pack (GS1 Permanent Code)
PR4.description: It is a promotional grouping with included free quantity. The grouping is created for promotional activities only. In the grouping a part of the quantity is free.

PRO.title: Programme (GS1 Permanent Code)
PRO.description: A programme within a Customer Specific Article which does not exist on its own.

RC.title: Returnable container (GS1 Permanent Code)
RC.description: The current product is not traditionally a traded product but one which should be returned according to separate instructions.

RD.title: Refundable deposit item (GS1 Permanent Code)
RD.description: Item is subject to a refundable deposit.

RE.title: Retail product (GS1 Permanent Code)
RE.description: The current item is meant for retail sale only, and not for sale to hotels, restaurants and catering.

RPC.title: Reusable pool container (GS1 Permanent Code)
RPC.description: Reusable container standardized by a pool cooperative.

SER.title: Service (GS1 Permanent Code)
SER.description: A code identifying the current item as a service (i.e. not a physical product).

SG.title: Standard group of products (mixed assortment) (GS1 Permanent Code)
SG.description: A standard package containing different products enabling the package to be ordered, delivered and invoiced.

SU.title: Smallest unit (GS1 Permanent Code)
SU.description: The smallest usable or tradeable size or unit for a given product.

TU.title: Traded unit (GS1 Permanent Code)
TU.description: The package size of a product or products which has been agreed by trading partners as the size which may be ordered, delivered and invoiced.

VQ.title: Variable quantity product (GS1 Permanent Code)
VQ.description: Product is used or traded in continuous rather than discrete quantities.

XX8.title: Fixed discount coupon on item price (GS1 Permanent Code)
XX8.description: A discount coupon that can be redeemed at the point of sale for a fixed amount when purchasing a specific item/brand/range.

XX9.title: Fixed discount coupon on purchase amount  (GS1 Permanent Code)
XX9.description: A discount coupon that can be redeemed at the point of sale for a fixed amount on the total amount of the purchase.

XY1.title: Percentage discount on item price  (GS1 Permanent Code)
XY1.description: A discount coupon that can be redeemed at the point of sale for a percentage of the specific item/brand/range value.

XY2.title: Percentage discount on purchase amount (GS1 Permanent Code)
XY2.description: A discount coupon that can be redeemed at the point of sale for a percentage of the total amount of the purchase.

XY3.title: Meal voucher (GS1 Permanent Code)
XY3.description: Fixed amount voucher that can be redeemed at foodservice industry.

XY4.title: Limited Edition (GS1 Permanent Code)
XY4.description: A product with limited edition is restricted in the number of copies produced, although in fact the number may be very low or very high. A special edition implies there is extra material of some kind included.

XY5.title: One Shot Product (GS1 Permanent Code)
XY5.description: The trading partners agree to supply/buy this product only once. Afterwards this product will not be supplied/bought any more

XY6.title: Fee (GS1 Permanent Code)
XY6.description: Code identify the GTIN of LIN segment as being fees.

XY7.title: Brokerage (GS1 Permanent Code)
XY7.description: Code identify the GTIN of LIN segment as being brokerages.

XY8.title: Transport medium unit (GS1 Permanent Code)
XY8.description: Code identify the position as a Transport Medium Unit (Pallet, Container, ....).

XY9.title: Counted measurand factor (GS1 Permanent Code)
XY9.description: Factor for price calculation  of energy products, e.g. gas, fuel.

XZ1.title: Standard condition conversion (GS1 Permanent Code)
XZ1.description: The ratio of a product volume (e.g. gas) in standard conditions to the volume in the operating state.

XZ2.title: Calorific value (GS1 Permanent Code)

COMPLIANT.title: Class Compliance Code (GS1 Permanent Code)
COMPLIANT.description: A code that indicates that a trade item is in compliance with specific applicable government regulations.

MATERIAL.title: Material Information (GS1 Permanent Code)
MATERIAL.description: This element is used to specify the quality of material (fabric) of a trade item.

ORGANIC.title: Organic Trade Item Code (GS1 Permanent Code)

PACKMAT.title: Packaging Material (GS1 Permanent Code)

UOM.title: Ordering and Selling Unit of Measure (GS1 Permanent Code)

European Communities - Commission Directive 98/11/EC of 27 January 1998.

X6.description: The household appliance is classified in energy efficiency class 'D'. European Communities - Commission Directive 98/11/EC of 27 January 1998.

X7.description: The household appliance is classified in energy efficiency class 'E'. European Communities - Commission Directive 98/11/EC of 27 January 1998.

X8.title: Energy efficiency class 'F' (GS1 Permanent Code)
X8.description: The household appliance is classified in energy efficiency class 'F'. European Communities - Commission Directive 98/11/EC of 27 January 1998.

X9.title: Energy efficiency class 'G' (GS1 Permanent Code)
X9.description: The household appliance is classified in energy efficiency class 'G'. The energy efficiency class is an indication of the energy consumption, expressed on a scale of A (more efficient) to G (less efficient). Ref. European Communities - Commission Directive 98/11/EC of 27 January 1998.
